text.section:
By resolution, the Board may specify the form in which State bonds are to be issued, including:
a coupon form;
a capital appreciation form;
a variable interest rate form;
a form that qualifies for tax credits, interest subsidies, or other federal tax benefits;
a form that qualifies as a registered form under §§ 54A, 103, and 149 of the Internal Revenue Code or a regulation proposed or adopted under those sections; and
any other registered form.
